 ON-AIR presenter, Toke Makinwa and Nollywood actress, Nancy Isime have been paired to host the third season of The Voice Nigeria. The TV reality and talent show has entered the third season with big financial support from First Bank of Nigeria. For this season, Yemi Alade, Waje, Falz, and Darey Art Alade return as the coaches that will be presiding over the fates of various budding musical talents. According to a statement from the organisers, registration for the blind auditions have been open till September 19. It was also gathered that for the first time, The Voice Nigeria will be produced in Nigeria with the ultimate winner getting a sum of N10 million cash prize, brand new car, and a recording deal with Universal Music.